              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Combined Pu-241- Pu-242 target, consisting of",
                " 26 ug/cm2 Pu-241 and 20 ug/cm2 Pu-242, sandwiched",
                " between 30 ug/cm2 thick polyimide backings.",
                " Pu-244, thickness 30 ug, sandwiched the same.",
                " Isotopic enrichments: Pu-241(91.0%),",
                " Pu-242(99.8%), Pu-244(87.6%)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC",
                "TOF",
                "STTA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                " Fast and slow coincidence to measure the pulse-",
                " heights of the fission fragments,",
                " For the thermal fission combined with time-of-",
                " flight difference between fission fragments, used",
                " as a coherence test to reject badly measured data.",
                " The combined Pu-241 / Pu-242 target was turned by",
                " 180 degree , when measuring the s.f.- data, in order",
                " to maintain the same energy loss conditions for",
                " both measurements."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                " Two cooled silicon surface barrier detectors.",
                " For energy calibration the natural alpha-lines",
                " of the Pu-isotopes were used."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Schmitt-Neiler calibration procedure (ref.",
                " C,65SALZBURG,1,531,1965) to convert pulse-heights to",
                " kinetic energies and masses.",
                " For the therm.fission the pre-neutron emission data",
                " were obtained via an iterative calculation described",
                " by Schmitt+ (PR,141,1146,1966). For the s.f. the data",
                " of Caitucoli+ (NP/A,369,15,1981) and Mughabghab and",
                " Garber,BNL 325(1973) were used (see REL-REF)."
              ]
            }
          ],
